# Commit Convention (Mandatory)

All commits must use Conventional Commits.

## Format

`<type>(<scope>): <short-description>`

Use lowercase for type and scope. Keep subject concise and imperative.

## Allowed types

- `feat`: new feature
- `fix`: bug fix
- `refactor`: internal code restructure without behavior change
- `docs`: documentation only
- `chore`: maintenance or non-feature changes
- `perf`: performance improvement
- `build`: build tooling or dependency changes
- `ci`: CI workflow changes
- `revert`: revert a previous commit

## Examples

- `feat(auth): add vendor staff invite endpoint`
- `fix(api): return 401 for expired sessions`
- `docs(api): update booking endpoint examples`
